==Abstract==

This IIP describes compact block relay, a method to reduce block propagation bandwidth by transmitting only short transaction identifiers. It is adapted from BIP 152 for INTcoin.

==Motivation==

Blocks often contain transactions already in the receiver's mempool. Compact blocks transmit short transaction IDs, allowing reconstruction from local mempool data, reducing bandwidth by ~90%.

==Specification==

===Messages===

'''sendcmpct''': Announce compact block support
<pre>
announce:    bool    // High-bandwidth mode
version:     uint64  // Protocol version (1 or 2)
</pre>

'''cmpctblock''': Compact block
<pre>
header:      CBlockHeader
nonce:       uint64
shortids:    []uint48      // 6-byte transaction IDs
prefilled:   []PrefilledTx // Transactions included in full
</pre>

'''getblocktxn''': Request missing transactions
<pre>
blockhash:   uint256
indexes:     []varint
</pre>

'''blocktxn''': Missing transactions response
<pre>
blockhash:   uint256
txs:         []CTransaction
</pre>

===Short ID Calculation===

<pre>
siphash_key = SHA3-256(header || nonce)[0:16]
shortid = SipHash-2-4(siphash_key, wtxid) & 0xffffffffffff
</pre>

===High-Bandwidth Mode===

In high-bandwidth mode, nodes send compact blocks immediately without waiting for a request, reducing latency for mining operations.

===INTcoin Adaptation===

* Uses SHA3-256 instead of SHA256 for key derivation
* wtxid computation uses SHA3-256

